Boil a very large #pot{} of water with your @chicken stock pot{1}. Once your stock pot
is fully dissolved, take out 360ml of stock and keep to the side for later. Put your
@brown basmati rice{2} in a #sieve{} (if you have one) and rinse under cold running
water for at least ~{30%seconds}. Cook the rice in the boiling stock for ~{25%minutes}.
Once the rice is cooked, drain it and put back in the empty pot off the heat.

Meanwhile, peel and chop your @garlic clove{2}(peeled and chopped), zest your
@lemon{1}(zested) and squeeze the juice into a separate #bowl{}. In another bowl,
mix the chopped garlic, lemon zest, @ground cumin{1}, @mild paprika{1.5%tsp} and a
quarter of the lemon juice along with @oil{4%tbsp} and stir. Put your
@British chicken thighs{6} into the bowl and mix it around making sure all the
chicken has a good coating.

> The best way to do this is to use your hands but do make sure you wash them properly
> after handling raw meat.

Cut the tough tops and bottoms off the @sugar snap peas{2}(trimmed) and pull the
stringy bits off the sides. Bring a pot of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for
later.

Heat @oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat and add the chicken. Cook
the chicken for ~{6%minutes} on each side until it is a lovely brown colour, then
take out of the pan and set aside on a #board{} or a #plate{} to rest. Cover with
#foil{} to keep warm.

Add the rest of the lemon juice to the pan along with the @honey{4}. Mix it around
and cook for ~{1-2%minutes} until slightly caramelised and sticky. Then add the
stock you reserved earlier in Step 1. Season with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@ground black pepper{grind}, stir, bring to a simmer and cook for ~{5-7%minutes},
until the sauce has reduced slightly.

While the sauce is reducing, add the sugar snap peas to your pot of boiling water
and cook for ~{4%minutes}, then drain.

Once you've drained your rice and put it back in the pot, add your
@baby spinach{6} and stir through to wilt it slightly. Cover the pot with a lid until
everything else is ready.

Cut your chicken into 2cm slices. Serve your spinach and brown rice with your chicken
and sauce on top and your sugar snap peas on the side.

> The sauce should soak through the rice to make it delicious and saucy.